    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-20T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-20T05:00:00-05:00" n="164"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d164">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 E. W. 1939/17739: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vichy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-20T12:00:00+02:00"
                            >December 20, 1941—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 4:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1578. Embassy’s 1530, 12th.<note n="8" xml:id="d164fn8">Not printed; this
                        telegram reported that notes containing declarations of war by the United
                        States against Germany and Italy were delivered at 5 p.m., December 12
                        (740.0011 European War 1939/17451).</note> In note to Embassy December 19
                    Foreign Office acknowledges Embassy’s communication notifying French Government
                    that state of war exists between the United States and Italy and states that it
                    is “the decision of the French Government to maintain in the course of this an
                    attitude of neutrality”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leahy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
